{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"opacity"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CDouble","preciseIdentifier":"s:s7CDoublea"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An opacity of 0 is fully transparent and an opacity of 1"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is fully opaque."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Opacity works on both toplevel widgets and child widgets, although"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"there are some limitations: For toplevel widgets, applying opacity"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"depends on the capabilities of the windowing system. On X11, this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"has any effect only on X displays with a compositing manager,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"see "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gdk_display_is_composited()"},{"type":"text","text":". On Windows and Wayland it should"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"always work, although setting a window’s opacity after the window"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"has been shown may cause some flicker."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that the opacity is inherited through inclusion — if you set"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a toplevel to be partially translucent, all of its content will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"appear translucent, since it is ultimatively rendered on that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"toplevel. The opacity value itself is not inherited by child"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"widgets (since that would make widgets deeper in the hierarchy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"progressively more translucent). As a consequence, [class"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.Popover"},{"type":"text","text":"]s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and other [iface"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.Native"},{"type":"text","text":"] widgets with their own surface will use their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"own opacity value, and thus by default appear non-translucent,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"even if they are attached to a toplevel that is translucent."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gtk\/passwordentryref\/set(opacity:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/PasswordEntryRef\/set(opacity:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Request the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"widget"},{"type":"text","text":" to be rendered partially transparent."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"set(opacity:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"opacity"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CDouble","preciseIdentifier":"s:s7CDoublea"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:3Gtk14WidgetProtocolPAAE3set7opacityySd_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3Gtk16PasswordEntryRefV","extendedModule":"Gtk","modules":[{"name":"Gtk"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/PasswordEntryRef","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/PasswordEntryRef\/WidgetProtocol-Implementations"]]},"referen